Two installation methods
========================

There are two installation methods. One (A) uses the default
libgphoto2 on the system. The other (B) can uses custom libgphoto2
installations and thus is a little more complicated in standalone
usage.

However, (B) is also integrated into gphoto-suite and thus
works with the libgphoto2 shipped with gphoto-suite.


A) Install libgphoto2-python using system's standard libgphoto2:
================================================================

   $ python setup.py build
   $ sudo python setup.py install
   $ make installcheck

   $ python gptest.py


B) Install libgphoto2-python using non-standard libgphoto2:
===========================================================

   $ mkdir __build && cd __build
   $ ../configure LIBGPHOTO2_CFLAGS="-I/path/to/include" LIBGPHOTO2_LIBS="-L/path/to/lib"
   $ make
   $ sudo make install
   $ make installcheck
